The Best in Arts
The Art Digest, Inc. | 1962 | English | 200 pages | PDF | 31.7 MB

A collection of critical essays, reviews, articles and memoirs, The Best in Arts brings together some of the most lively and refreshing writing from the pages of ARTS Magazine. Selected by the Editor of ARTS and with an introduction by Hilton Kramer, this volume of essays includes: Eight Articles on Various Topics Lavishly illustrated essays on a variety painting and the early Flemish masters to the avant-garde art of the Russian Revolution
